	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />IIRC a company doesn't have to pay import duties (or at least they get significantly lower) when shipping their products to Brazil if a certain minimum amount of the products' development takes place in Brazil.
<br />
<br />I know for a fact that another consumer electronics company opened up a Brazil office a few years ago and moved some software projects there for that specific purpose - even with the disturbances that would cause to the development. Then the global financial crisis hit and no one in Brazil could afford to buy shit from them anyway. Oh the irony.

		

