		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I blame Ronaldo.
<br />
<br />On a more serious note, similar prices (though not as inflated, but close!) are seen in post-socialist countries in the EU, like Sweden.  This is especially the case for technological/electronic devices.  There, it's actually cheaper to buy something in the US + pay international shipping rates + pay VAT than to buy it local.
<br />
<br />Though, in their case, I believe the markup is a result of vendors charging absurd amounts of money "just because they can".  I don't know what's going on in Brazil, but it could be something like that.
<br />
<br />If you ever want something from the US, let me know -- I ship stuff out internationally fairly often.

		

		</td>
